Interface IDefinitionSet

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IMutableDefinitionSet
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AccessorDefinition, AmbiguousDefinition, AppliedVectorDefinition, ASProjectScope.DefinitionPromise, ClassDefinition, ClassDefinitionBase, ClassTraitsDefinition, ConstantDefinition, DefinitionBase, EffectDefinition, EventDefinition, FunctionDefinition, GetterDefinition, InterfaceDefinition, LargeDefinitionSet, MemberedDefinition, MetadataDefinitionBase, NamespaceDefinition, PackageDefinition, ParameterDefinition, ScopedDefinitionBase, SetterDefinition, SmallDefinitionSet, StateDefinition, StateDefinitionBase, StateGroupDefinition, StyleDefinition, SyntheticBindableGetterDefinition, SyntheticBindableSetterDefinition, TypeDefinitionBase, VariableDefinition

    public interface IDefinitionSet
    This interface represents an immutable collection of definitions with the same base name in a particular scope.

    It's really more of a List than a Set because it is indexable.
